le understanding the layout (which I personally find very well done) it's important to pay attention and really look at each frame carefully. If you still don't understand, why not move on, then come back later? It's not the best way to read manga, and if you really just can't stand the flow, perhaps you should leave it alone for a while.<br>
Really though, the beautiful, flexible, and greately varied art, fresh, innovative presentation and greatly relatable characters have me hooked into Naruto. The story has depth, but is also easy to follow and has a good deal of humor and subtle irony running around- For example, Naruto actually wears bright colors, shouts a lot, and is blonde- nowhere near the stereotype of a ninja. By not restraining itself to the old ideas of what a good ninja or ninjitsu is, Kishimoto's manga can really take a somewhat old, over-used idea and make it fresh and really crazy-fun.<br>
But i'm so in love with it, if you honestly don't like it, don't take my word for it.<br>
I can't speak for the anime though, and I may never see it so as not to sully my adoration for the manga... It's kind of like how I thought Inu yasha was pretty good, but because of the anime (and the CONSTANT recap) I'm not too fond of it anymore. A bit of a shame, that... Not to mention the previously noticed rabid fanbase... =_=<br>
Think I'll tread softly and avoid that subject entirely. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mamoruk>MamoruK</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/3/04 8:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2690.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> oh i totaly agree that theres much beter series out there, but i still like this one. im not fanatic over it but i do enjoy it whole heartily. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azmaguta>Azmaguta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/4/04 2:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2690.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> konekonomidori: I disagree. It's the fact that he uses ALL the tired of old clichès that I dislike it. The Naruto character is seen all over the place. Yahiko in Kenshin, that kid in HxH, and the main character in Peacekeeper something. They're all &quot;I'm going to surpass blah blah blah&quot;, and they reach an incredible amount of skill in no time. As for the art, I really can't say I like it. The characters are mostly bland and unattractive to look at, an